<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>EnOTDIR on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/enotdir/</link><description>Recent content in EnOTDIR on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/enotdir/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C errno ENOTDIR — Not a directory Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-enotdir/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-enotdir/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-errno-enotdir--not-a-directory-fix"&gt;[Solution] C errno ENOTDIR — Not a directory Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When a path component that is expected to be a directory is actually not a directory, the system call fails and sets &lt;code&gt;errno&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code&gt;ENOTDIR&lt;/code&gt;. This error typically occurs during path resolution when a non-directory file is encountered where a directory is required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A component in the path is a regular file, not a directory (e.g., &lt;code&gt;open(&amp;quot;file.txt/subdir&amp;quot;, ...)&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using &lt;code&gt;chdir()&lt;/code&gt; on a path where an intermediate component is not a directory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calling &lt;code&gt;opendir()&lt;/code&gt; on a regular file instead of a directory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;execve()&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;readdir()&lt;/code&gt; receives a path with a non-directory component.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Verify that each path component is a directory before performing directory operations. Use &lt;code&gt;stat()&lt;/code&gt; to check the file type.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C Not a directory: ENOTDIR</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/not-a-directory/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/not-a-directory/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="not-a-directory-enotdir"&gt;Not a directory: ENOTDIR&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ENOTDIR occurs when a path component that should be a directory is actually a regular file, or when trying to access a file as if it were in a directory path.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Path component is a file, not directory
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// /home/user/file.txt is a regular file
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Trying to access /home/user/file.txt/subdir
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;open&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;/home/user/file.txt/subdir/file.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, O_RDONLY); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ENOTDIR
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Wrong path separator
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;open&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;file.txt/subdir&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, O_RDONLY); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ENOTDIR
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Symlink points to file, not directory
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// symlink(&amp;#34;file.txt&amp;#34;, &amp;#34;mylink&amp;#34;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Trying to access mylink/subdir
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-verify-path-components"&gt;Fix 1: Verify path components&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;struct&lt;/span&gt; stat st;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;stat&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;/home/user&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;st);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;S_ISDIR&lt;/span&gt;(st.st_mode)) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fprintf&lt;/span&gt;(stderr, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Not a directory: /home/user&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-check-path-before-using"&gt;Fix 2: Check path before using&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;path &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;/home/user/file.txt/subdir&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Split and check each component
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-correct-paths"&gt;Fix 3: Use correct paths&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; fd &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;open&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;/home/user/subdir/file.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, O_RDONLY);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/is-a-directory/"&gt;Is a directory&lt;/a&gt; — EISDIR.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/no-such-file/"&gt;No such file&lt;/a&gt; — ENOENT.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/symbolic-link-loop/"&gt;Too many symbolic links&lt;/a&gt; — ELOOP.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Linux ENOTDIR (errno 20) — Not a Directory Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-20/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-20/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="linux-enotdir-errno-20--not-a-directory"&gt;Linux ENOTDIR (errno 20) — Not a Directory&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ENOTDIR (errno 20) means a component of the path used in an operation is not a directory when it was expected to be. This error occurs when you try to use a file as if it were a directory, such as listing its contents or creating a path through it. It is distinct from ENOENT (errno 2) because the file exists but is not a directory.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>